result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Daniel L Schickert was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. 9:20 AM Court recalls case. Defendant Daniel L Schickert in court.  Attorney Daniel M Key in court for Daniel L Schickert.  Attorney Luke Steiner in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Court cancels warrant that was issued earlier.
Defendant is heard on being late to court. Apologizes to court as ride was late. 
Attorney Key is heard and they are ready to move forward with plea and sentencing. 

Court reviews plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form with defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the constitutional and fundamental rights with Defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the elements of the charge with defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the minimum / maximum penalties with defendant. Defendant states understanding. 

Court asks defendant for plea. Defendant enters a no contest plea. Court accepts the defendants no contest plea and finds that the defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily enters plea. Court finds the defendant guilty of count 1. Court will dismiss count 2. 

Ct 1 - 346.63(1)(a) - Operating While under the Influence (1) NO CONTEST 
Ct 2 - 346.63(1)(b) - Operating with PAC (1) DISMISSED 

State will remain silent on sentencing.  State is heard on the lab results, .206.  Blood draw was done at CR.
Attorney Key is heard on sentencing, requests that sentence be imposed and stayed. Attorney Key requests probation which includes treatment court for the defendant. 2 days credit. 

Court orders an imposed and stayed 4 yr prison sentence.  2 yr initial confinement, 2 year extended supervision. Sentence stayed and Defendant to be placed on probation for 3 years. 
Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages. Participate in any other assessments as deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections and follow through with recommended counseling, treatment or programming. Complete all programming from the CC Treatment Court. 1 year in the county jail. First 6 months of that jail sentence will be without work release. The second six months defendant is entitled to electronic monitoring. 2 days jail credit on conditional jail. Court approves defendant to serve in another county if defendant chooses. Fine of $2,000.00 plus costs  Blood draw fee of $120.00.  Total of 3,713.00 due April 15th, 2023. Court will approve a payment plan. Defendant can request/set the payment plan at that time. (NOT cond of probation - 36 mo of DL rev. AODA assessment). $250.00 bond will be applied. Defendant remanded from court.
